After seeing 4.9 as an overall rating for this restaurant, I wanted to try it out.  I'm Greek, so i have a true understanding of what Greek food should taste like, and unfortunately - as with most Greek restaurants outside of Astoria - the food here is simply OK.  Let's start with the 5 star items:  - Very friendly staff with what appears to be a true interest in keeping patrons happy (based on my interaction, and what I saw with other tables) - Lovely backyard patio and decor,, as well as some tables on Flushing Ave. - Clean and appropriate social distancing. - Prices are very good and portions are nicely sized. - Grilled Octopus was excellent.  Now to the 3 star items:  - Red Sangria was ok.  Nicely priced for $4 for Happy Hour, however way too much ice in the glass (so you end up having to get more). - Keftedakia (Greek style meatballs) were also ok.  Seasoning wasn't apparent and they were slightly over cooked on the outside. - The Tzatziki was nice, as was the Pita Bread.  Now to the 1.5 star items" - The Fried Calamari was tasteless, too crunchy, and came out way too quick after ordering.  Seems like it was pre cooked and left standing.  No way it can be prepped within 5 minutes of ordering.  Absolutely not worth trying at all. - The Saganaki (Fried Cheese) would have been better had it not had a strong taste of liquor (its a flambe situation) that leaves an awful aftertaste.  Not sure what other items taste like, but based on my experience today, I'd be hesitant to go back.

Adan is one of the best owners I have ever worked with and I am a foodie . The restaurant ambience it AMAZING . Big portions , full of flavor , and the right price . He will cater all over the 5 boroughs also! Definitely Bushwick’s hot spot . Summer time I can’t wait for the patio !

Amazing food, big portions, super friendly staff. All the ingredients are extremely fresh and every part of the dish is home-cooked. The fried zucchini and eggplant was not as crunchy as I had imagined, but was delicious nonetheless. One gyro plate plus one entree for 2 is more than enough.

The food was absolutely delicious! We got the tzatziki dip, Poseidon platter, and lamb kebab. All the dishes were very delicious.  The owner was extremely friendly and chatted with us multiple times throughout the meal. Highly recommend if you are in the area or nearby.
Nice ambient and the chicken was delicious
Excellent Greek authentic food. So fresh and delicious. A true neighborhood find

The food was simply delicious. The portions were more than we thought they would be. Would definitely say if you like Greek food you will enjoy this place. Can't wait until the spring and summer time, they have a outdoor seating area 😁😆 the service was great too and the manager/owner was very attentive to our party of 8.

Very kind staff, they treat you like family there. The food is always great and sometimes they'll give you dessert or extra pita, just like your grandmother would at her house. The music they play feeds well into the ambiance. For appetizers, the four cheese balls and the stuffed grape leaves are pretty good, aside from the classic hummus and pita. I always like getting the biftekia or a chicken gyro as my entree. The plates come with quite a bit of food so take your time, sit down and enjoy it. For desserts, the baklava and rice pudding are pretty good. I've also had the Greek yogurt with cranberry jam, bittersweet but also a nice option.

I've only eaten there once, but order fairly regularly. The food is so good! All of the dips are delicious and they're very generous with the pita portions. Eating there was cool because you can see the doner rotating on the spit. Service was great. This is a welcome addition to the neighborhood!!

Fresh, delicious and generous portions this restaurant is a gem! I had th chicken kabob with sauteed spinach, my husband had the Donder platter and was impressed with how perfect everythin was. The service also didn't miss a beat. The waiter was attentive and the owner really cared that we enjoyed our dinner. Anytime we visit our daughter in Brooklyn this will be our go to place!

I have ordered from here a few times and have gone once. My expoernce in house was amazing. Service was very friendly and attentive. They made great suggestions and even treated us to some great yogurt after the meal. The meatballs are fantastic. Great crisp and flavor. The tzatziki sauce is so darn good and refreshing. It is also one of the few places where the food is just as good delivered as in person. Still very warm and fresh. Can’t wait to eat there again.
Everything is delicious!
Incredible food made with fresh ingredients at reasonable prices... I can’t wait to come back!
Great lamb meals! Owner is super cool.
This is the best Greek restaurant in New York. It’s not even close.
Good
Great service and delicious food!
The food was great and something different, it's really modern inside the place and the service was great
The best Greek delivery! They are always SO nice and the food is 100% consistent and on point. Thank you guys!!!
Great greek spot!

We were just there last night and amazed with service and food quality! The owner goes out of his way to make sure you enjoy your experience. The portions are well sized and they also offer pita and olives/hummus appetizers so you will not leave hungry! I am still having my platter today for lunch. The gyro platter tastes amazing and they also have a few traditional dishes that a lot of gyro places don’t. Highly recommend.

This place competes between having great hospitality and great food. The chicken gyro hit all the right notes and the Doner gyro packed in a punch of flavors. The people were really friendly and we felt like this was our regular spot, even though it was our first visit. + the sangria is a winner!
Cosy place that you can find classic Greek menu. Friendly and professional staff. Great porsion sizes. They don't serve Ouzo.
Wow. Great great place and food. Generous portions.
Very good greek food here, great service
Awesome spot go for it you wont regret it

it’s my favorite spot for Authentic Greek  in Brooklyn. The Lemon potatoes are cooked to perfection with a beautiful fragrant flavor and their chicken Slovaki is tender and definitely seasoned with love.
This place is phenomenal. Amazing service. I can't wait to go back.

I’ve been meaning to write a review for this place since visiting NYC with my friend and deciding on a whim to go somewhere nicer for dinner with a couple of other people.  First of all, the overall environment was just warm and welcoming. The servers were all very kind and patient when explaining the menu items, and they even treated us with an appetizer while we waited for our other friends to arrive.  The owner came out and thanked us for visiting the restaurant, which I thought was such an exceptional gesture. Honestly. Here I am a couple of weeks later, and this still sticks in my mind as a genuine act of going above and beyond. A-plus customer service. We truly felt that our patronage was appreciated.  Food was fantastic. Portions were huge. We all left feeling full and satisfied and in good spirits from the positive dining experience. We all ordered different entrées, and we were all happy with what we had chosen.  I never write reviews, but I wanted to make sure I wrote one for this restaurant. I don’t live in NYC anymore, but I visit frequently, and you can bet I’ll be back! :-)
Excellent food, friendly staff! Owner greeted us personally and thanked us for taking the time to try the food. Will definitely return.
Love all the food and amazing dessert, very good attention. The lamb and lasagna were soo tasty
Great addition to the neighborhood. Homey, tasty Greek food. Owner is super nice and the staff is helpful, competent and friendly.
I had such an amazing time eating this amazing food!!

Definitely a great experience trying Greek food at this restaurant. Very nice environment for a dinner date with friends, family or significant other and such a beautiful decor all around. Their attention to detail when it comes to taking care of you is absolutely exceptional. Their food is beyond what words can describe. You can taste how fresh it is and all the seasoning that was added to make its delicious taste. Definitely recommend anyone who’s wanting to try Greek food to come here. Amazing experience!!
The food here is EXCELLENT! I have been here a few times now and have yet to try a dish that was not delish. The owner and people who work here are very welcoming and they have a nice patio as well.

First time visiting Yia Yia's and was very impressed. The outdoor space is very relaxed and a perfect spot to have your meal. The owner even came and greeted us personally and was a gentleman. I'll definitely be back.
The best Greek spot in the neighborhood
Good food, friendly workers and outdoor area
The kitchen is very clean that means a lot
Very nice staff, tasty food, and generous portions.  I've gone several times now, and they are consistently good.
Food is excellent and back garden is gorgeous!  The owner came out to ask how my meal was and sent everyone out a taste of their fantastic rice pudding.  Will definitely be back!
Hey this is Miriam from the Brooklyn Agency sayng Hi it is a real pleasure working with you guys!!!!!!
Great new Greek spot in Bushwick!! All the food we had was delicious, and the service was excellent. The owner came to check and make sure we were satisfied with everything. Will definitely be back
Service, food, dessert... amazing.

Lots of delicious vegan & vegetarian options. My mom & I ordered nearly everything on the menu and loved it, so this review oughtta count as 10 stars (-: We're part Turkish, so it's nice to have Greek food (very similar cuisine) come to the neighborhood. We get tired of making our own stuffed grape leaves & falafel, lol. I love that it's authentic and not pretentious whatsoever. Just totally chill & very nice atmosphere. Super nice staff too! & wonderfully hospitable owner. Μπορείτε να δείτε πολλά χρόνια επιτυχίας! (Cheers to many years of success!)
The best new restaurant in Bushwick. All star service, incredible and authentic food - just the perfect spot. Definitely unassuming from the outside but you won’t be sorry if you stop in for a bite!
Great staff and amazing food!
Delicious food and very friendly staff.

This place is amazing- my new favorite Bushwick spot.  Owner is a great guy- a Mexican who married into a Greek family and spent years there- he now makes the best Lemon Chicken Soup I've ever had (can't wait for winter) and the creamiest Mousaka I've ever had.  Can't wait to come back and try rest of the menu.  Must go.

Delicious authentic Greek food. A real taste of the Mediterranean in bk.

Beautiful is the word when describing this new Greek establishment. The food is fresh and wonderfully prepared whilst being served by a staff of absolutely delightful people. The decor is classic, clean and well lit. A must try!  Try the frappe. A bold and delicious treat that is perfectly crafted and sure to please!

Love this place & food so much, I'm making up excuses to have it 2 times a week. The staff is extremely friendly and amazing! Plus they have outdoor seating if you feel like having your meal al fresco. This is exactly what the neighborhood needed.
Great food, incredible service
INCREDIBLE FOOD. INCREDIBLE SERVICE. GREAT PRICES. GO THERE RIGHT NOW. NOW. GO.
Best Greek food in Brooklyn!!!!!! I never write reviews but this is too good!! Nicest people, cute backyard, delicious home made food. They deliver too.

I'm almost hesitant to write this as I have a feeling this place is going to be swarmed very, very soon. I can't help myself though, this place is AMAZING. Real deal Astoria Greek food in a nice welcoming atmosphere (they even have an outdoor area) that isn't run by sullen looking tattooed hipsters trying to charge me obscene prices for tiny portions while they pump out bland indie rock and do their best to pretend they don't work in a restaurant. Nope. Here you'll get friendly people who actually care about the food they're serving, and healthy portions of absolutely perfect Greek food. I've never been to Athens, but I am 100% certain this what the food would taste like if you crashed a party at someone's Grandma's house.
The Best Greek food, I love it... I will be back 😍
EXCELLENT SERVICE. BEST GYRO IN BROOKLYN FOR SURE. BEEN BACK SEVERAL TIME SINCE OPENING!! HIGHLY RECOMMENDED !!!

Best chicken gyro I ever had. They also give a free tapas/appetizer of pita, olive oil, and olives which is actually a lot of food and a huge plus. I read their menu passing by and decided to give it a try. I was greeted immediately, and informed the the restaurant had only been open for two days. I was blown away by the service and food. I returned the next two days in a row, and am sure I will be back many times after. It was fairly empty in the restaurant the times I went in, probably has something to do with them being new, or maybe the hours I went. People need to give this place a try.

We stumbled upon this place while walking around the area and discovered a gem. It was impeccable food paired with wonderful service. The donair is not processed meat but a combination of lamb and beef which is often not found. The garlic feta dip is delightfully spicy, something I haven’t had anywhere else. Defiantly something I will come back for.
